             butcher, Osborne street.</p>
               <p>Q. When did you loose your beef - A. On Saturday night the 21st of January, about ten o'clock in the evening. The prisoner ran up to the side of the stall and took the beef off the board; he took it, and run away with it, my father pursued him and took him with the beef upon him.</p>
               <p>Prisonor's Defence. I am a poor man, I am lost for want of a friend to come and speak for me, I had no beef upon me, when I was taken, I never took the beef.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150215-76-person644">
                  Robert 
                  Marryon
               <interp inst="t18150215-76-person644" type="surname" value="Marryon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150215-76-person644" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150215-76-person644" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am sure he is the same man, he had the beef in his possession; when my father took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150215-76-person645">
                  WILLIAM 
                  GALE
               <interp inst="t18150215-76-person645" type="surname" value="GALE"></interp>
